&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an exceptional &lt;strong&gt;Accounts Receivable Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to join our organization at Accredited Labs.&amp;nbsp;This is a unique opportunity to be part of a fast-growing team and have a direct impact on &lt;strong&gt;cash flow optimization, financial accuracy, and customer account management&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have &lt;strong&gt;strong leadership skills, deep expertise in accounts receivable processes, and the ability to drive efficiency in a fast-paced environment&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based out of Dallas, TX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our &lt;strong&gt;Accounts Receivable Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be &lt;strong&gt;responsible for overseeing invoicing, collections, and cash application functions&lt;/strong&gt;. This role is pivotal in &lt;strong&gt;ensuring financial stability, minimizing credit risk, and supporting overall organizational performance&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DAY TO DAY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee daily operations of the accounts receivable function, including billing, collections, dispute resolution, and cash application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely invoicing and accurate recording of receivables in accordance with internal policies and accounting standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor aging reports and drive collection strategies to improve cash flow and reduce delinquency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement policies, procedures, and performance metrics to enhance efficiency and effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess customer creditworthiness and establish appropriate credit limits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile accounts and resolve billing discrepancies in coordination with internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support month-end and year-end close processes, including reconciliations and audit preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop the accounts receivable team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASIC QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of accounts receivable experience, including at least 2 years in a leadership role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of accounting principles, credit analysis, and collections strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with ERP systems (NetSuite preferred) and advanced Microsoft Excel skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational, analytical, and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NICE TO HAVE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA or MBA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in high-volume, multi-entity, or complex business environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with automation tools that improve accounts receivable processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BENEFITS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Insurance&lt;br&gt;Comprehensive medical coverage to support your well-being&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dental Insurance&lt;br&gt;Preventive and restorative care to keep you smiling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vision Insurance&lt;br&gt;Coverage for eye exams, glasses, and contacts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;401(k) with Company Match&lt;br&gt;Plan for your future with our retirement savings plan and generous employer match&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Company-Paid Life Insurance&lt;br&gt;Peace of mind with fully covered life insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paid Time Off (PTO)&lt;br&gt;Enjoy a healthy work-life balance with paid time off&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paid Holidays&lt;br&gt;Celebrate and recharge with paid company holidays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Company-Provided Equip

