&lt;section class=&quot;styles--3vx-H&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ETI Precision is looking for a talented calibration technician to join its team in Charlotte! This is a full-time role offering competitive pay and great benefits. Calibration Technician - Level0/Level I/Level II/Level III will test, calibrate, and troubleshoot a variety of test and measurement instruments. This critical equipment is maintained and periodically calibrated for accuracy, reliability, and conformance to established industry and customer standards. As a calibration technician, you will be relied upon by both our customers and your colleagues within an environment that values professional development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; On-site at various customer sites in &lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Huntersville, NC&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and surrounding areas. Occasionally at our office in &lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Huntersville, NC&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Calibration Technician - Level I/Level II/Level III will primarily be responsible for the calibration of electronic and mechanical test equipment, at our customers’ facilities. This job requires travel. Key responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan the sequence of testing and calibration procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calibrate, adjust, and troubleshoot problems with customers’ equipment, including electrical, mechanical, pressure, torque, environmental, dimensional, and radio frequency instrumentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, update, and maintain data sheets for test equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain customer, vendor, and equipment databases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage customer relationships, ensure customer satisfaction, and drive the timely turnaround of equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;styles--3vx-H&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-requirements&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education, Experience &amp;amp; Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level II and above: at least two years of experience in a related field required. Electronics technician experience strongly preferred. Electrical, electronic, or mechanical calibration experience as well as military PMEL, METCAL, or TMDE training preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level II and above: technical knowledge of electronic principles. Experience using diagrams, schematics, engineering data, and test equipment is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability and willingness to travel to customers’ locations throughout the United States for up to one week at a time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An entrepreneurial attitude and desire to grow within an organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must possess a valid driver’s license and pass a background security check.&lt;/li&gt;
