&lt;p&gt;ATSNUC, Inc. is seeking a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Calibration Technician&lt;/strong&gt; to support daily calibration and service operations while remaining primarily hands‑on in technical work. This role focuses on advanced calibration execution, technical oversight, and supporting team consistency, ensuring all work meets regulatory, quality, and customer expectations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is ideal for an experienced technician with &lt;strong&gt;5+ years of calibration experience&lt;/strong&gt;, including &lt;strong&gt;Nuclear Density Gauges&lt;/strong&gt;, who is ready to take on a lead role—guiding others, setting technical standards, and owning work quality without full managerial responsibility.&lt;/p&gt;
